reviews.review_text:
Unique and Spacey - for 85 fans I really enjoyed this show, especially because it was so unique at times - especially for 85. That's what makes this such a super show for fans of 85.

The best parts really get going starting with "Bob Jam" !!

oh yeah!!!! Are you kidding me ? The best Sugaree I've ever heard, it takes me back to that special time when all that mattered was being inside at a show to hear Jerry sing and play like that. Those were the days my freind, we thought they'd never end. I remember walking aimlessly around the lot after that show thinking "did you just see what I just saw"? Passion baby , pure Passion. Forever Grateful Forever Dead .

Grateful ...for finding this gem.

Excellent venue, hands down, for any band.
Sound system is the shyte, and they always have it locked down.

The boys are obviously on fire from the first notes, and I think, also, the whole second set, particularly Terrapin through Good Lovin' is choice.

Dig that, huh? Good Lovin closes out second set, with Keep Your Day Job as the encore.

Download, stream, listen, and love.
See you guys in spring/summer.  *crosses fingers*
Good, but nowhere near the quality of the Dave Cohen copy.
